      "targetText": "acces"
    }
  ],
  "antonyms": [
    {
      "sourceText": "include",
      "targetText": "a include"
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
    {
      "sourceText": "I exclude you.",
      "targetText": "Te exclud."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "Do you exclude her?",
      "targetText": "O excluzi?"
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "He excludes the members.",
      "targetText": "El exclude membrii."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "We exclude all possibilities.",
      "targetText": "Noi excludem toate posibilitățile."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "Do you exclude the chances?",
      "targetText": "Excludeti oportunitățile?"
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "They exclude the access.",
      "targetText": "Ei exclud accesul."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "I have excluded him.",
      "targetText": "L-am exclus."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "They often excluded me.",
      "targetText": "Ei mă excluzau adesea."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "I will exclude you.",
      "targetText": "Te voi exclude."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "I would exclude the offer.",
      "targetText": "Aș exclude oferta."
    },
    {
      "sourceText": "Exclude that!",
      "targetText": "Exclu acest lucru!"
    }
  ],
  "learningTips": [
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Think of 'exclude' as 'ex' (out) + 'clude' (close) — to close someone out of a group or activity."
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Remember that 'a exclude' is like 'exclude' in English, making it easier to recall its meaning of keeping someone or something out."
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The ending '-e' in 'excludem' sounds like the English 'em' in 'them,' helping you associate it with 'we exclude.'"
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Imagine a club door closing on someone to 'exclude' them — this visual helps link the Romanian verb to its meaning."
    }
  ],
